I.	Introduction
A Risk Management Program has been implemented at the Metropolitan Pier and Exposition Authority (MPEA) Energy Center, located at 2211 South Martin Luther King Jr. Drive in Chicago, Illinois, for the reduction of accidental releases of hazardous materials. This updated, five (5) year Risk Management Plan (RMP) summarizes the management, administrative, procedural, and technological controls that work together to minimize the risk to site personnel, contractors, visitors, and the community and environment at large of hazardous chemical releases. The RMP is organized to correspond with specific U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) RMP, Program 3 of 40 CFR 68, definitions and requirements of Subpart G, including: 
¿	Introduction;
¿	MPEA policies to protect health, environment, and safety;
¿	Facility identification and regulated substances covered processes;
¿	Hazard Assessment;
¿	Prevention Program;
¿	Five-Year Accident History;
¿	Emergency Response Plan; 
¿	Emergency Communications;
¿	Spill Reporting / Environmental Release Procedures;
¿	Planned changes to improve safety; and
¿	Management Program

II.	MPEA Policies To Protect Health, Environment, and Safety
Risk management and safety are important concerns at the MPEA Energy Center; this RMP formalizes and documents these activities. The MPEA Energy Center is committed to conducting its operations in a safe and responsible manner and to reducing risks to human health and to the environment. It is the MPEA Energy Center's policy to comply with all applicable federal, state, and local rules and regulations.  This updated risk management plan is being submitted to comply with EPA 40 CFR 68 requirements to submit a risk management plan, every five (5) years.

